{meta: title I Hardly Knew it was You}
{meta: artist Faron Young}
{meta: composer Dan Welch}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Tinted hair and painted lips
[G7]Polish on your fingertips
[C]I hardly knew it was you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
Shabby dress and worn out gloves
[G7]A shadow of the girl I love
[C]I hardly knew it was you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]You once said that you would have no [C]one
[D7]Now no one will ever have [G7]you
[C]A life of hardship and disgrace
[G7]I see it written on your face
[C]I hardly knew it was you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
Custom jewels and cheap perfume
[G7]You're like a rose that's lost its bloom
[C]I hardly knew it was you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
From the simple girl I knew
[G7]You have changed dear through and through
[C]I hardly knew it was you
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[F]We could have lived our lives [C]together
[D7]But your heart had a mind all its [G7]own
[C]What a pity what a shame
[G7]I don't know who's to blame
[C]But I hardly knew it was you
{end_of_verse}
